1
00:01:32,640 --> 00:01:35,040
=Love Again=

2
00:01:35,266 --> 00:01:38,150
=Episode 8=

3
00:01:38,153 --> 00:01:38,829
Come on.

4
00:01:38,830 --> 00:01:39,933
- Raise...
- I've noticed

5
00:01:40,022 --> 00:01:42,230
you have become a good drinker now.

6
00:01:42,233 --> 00:01:43,112
Take a look at me.

7
00:01:43,112 --> 00:01:45,353
If you're healthy, you can drink.

8
00:01:45,353 --> 00:01:46,472
I can't hold my liquor well.

9
00:01:50,312 --> 00:01:51,873
Have you told her about getting married?

10
00:01:53,312 --> 00:01:53,793
No.

11
00:01:55,392 --> 00:01:57,112
Why are you hesitating?

12
00:01:58,155 --> 00:01:59,070
I'm not hesitating.

13
00:01:59,073 --> 00:02:01,593
Marriage needs the right timing.

14
00:02:01,593 --> 00:02:03,312
She's getting food for you. Quick.

15
00:02:04,993 --> 00:02:05,272
Come.

16
00:02:05,672 --> 00:02:07,832
You always let others take care of you.

17
00:02:07,832 --> 00:02:08,313
No.

18
00:02:08,513 --> 00:02:09,392
Look.

19
00:02:09,592 --> 00:02:10,429
He's scolding me.

20
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:11,288
Don't worry about me.

21
00:02:11,313 --> 00:02:11,913
Eat your food.

22
00:02:12,552 --> 00:02:13,992
The fish is really good.

23
00:02:13,992 --> 00:02:14,552
Okay.

24
00:02:14,672 --> 00:02:15,829
Why aren't you eating prawns?

25
00:02:15,830 --> 00:02:16,777
Let me peel one for you.

26
00:02:17,155 --> 00:02:18,592
No need to take care of me. I got it.

27
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:21,488
What's wrong?

28
00:02:23,733 --> 00:02:24,270
Look at you.

29
00:02:24,272 --> 00:02:25,552
You pricked yourself.

30
00:02:25,753 --> 00:02:26,953
It's nothing. Just a small cut.

31
00:02:28,392 --> 00:02:28,872
I'm good.

32
00:02:29,953 --> 00:02:31,033
Stay still. Look at this.

33
00:02:31,112 --> 00:02:32,992
Don't be stubborn.

34
00:02:33,432 --> 00:02:34,152
You're bleeding.

35
00:02:37,913 --> 00:02:39,152
All right.

36
00:02:41,353 --> 00:02:43,913
We used to suck out the blood.

37
00:02:44,313 --> 00:02:45,992
It's okay.

38
00:02:45,992 --> 00:02:46,793
Just a minor cut.

39
00:02:47,592 --> 00:02:48,033
Excuse me.

40
00:02:48,272 --> 00:02:49,432
Do you have

41
00:02:49,712 --> 00:02:51,353
band-aids and alcohol?

42
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,490
I'll take you to get some.

43
00:02:52,490 --> 00:02:53,150
- OK.
- No need.

44
00:02:53,152 --> 00:02:54,112
Let's go. Come with me.

45
00:02:54,432 --> 00:02:55,672
You keep eating.

46
00:02:55,688 --> 00:02:56,830
I'll go take care of her wound.

47
00:02:56,832 --> 00:02:57,513
It's bleeding.

48
00:02:58,152 --> 00:02:58,712
I'm sorry.

49
00:02:58,913 --> 00:02:59,633
It's fine.

50
00:03:02,112 --> 00:03:03,112
He cares about her.

51
00:03:03,313 --> 00:03:04,233
Look at them.

52
00:03:04,672 --> 00:03:05,872
"Don't be stubborn."

53
00:03:06,473 --> 00:03:08,033
"Look, you're bleeding."

54
00:03:09,872 --> 00:03:10,592
So cheesy.

55
00:03:11,112 --> 00:03:12,152
They're acting silly.

56
00:03:12,392 --> 00:03:13,313
Are you jealous?

57
00:03:13,992 --> 00:03:15,992
Shen is a happy man.

58
00:03:16,672 --> 00:03:17,552
Happy man.

59
00:03:17,872 --> 00:03:18,872
Come on. Let's toast.

60
00:03:18,872 --> 00:03:19,793
Come on.

61
00:03:19,953 --> 00:03:20,473
Cheers.

62
00:03:20,953 --> 00:03:22,193
Given our age,

63
00:03:22,444 --> 00:03:23,990
we're frequent visitors to the hospital.

64
00:03:24,592 --> 00:03:25,633
So gatherings like this

65
00:03:25,712 --> 00:03:27,193
should become the norm.

66
00:03:28,272 --> 00:03:29,432
The older we get,

67
00:03:29,913 --> 00:03:31,313
the fewer chances we get to meet.

68
00:03:31,592 --> 00:03:33,793
We need to get together
more often, don't you think?

69
00:03:33,793 --> 00:03:34,353
Yes.

70
00:03:35,073 --> 00:03:35,712
Come on.

71
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,311
You need to drink as a penalty.

72
00:03:38,311 --> 00:03:38,750
Drink.

73
00:03:38,753 --> 00:03:39,592
I'll drink.

74
00:03:39,913 --> 00:03:40,552
All right.

75
00:03:40,933 --> 00:03:41,950
You're drinking again?

76
00:03:42,233 --> 00:03:43,592
You must drink, Shen.

77
00:03:43,832 --> 00:03:44,592
One full glass.

78
00:03:45,033 --> 00:03:45,392
Drink.

79
00:03:45,392 --> 00:03:46,633
I'll drink.

80
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:47,592
I'll drink by myself.

81
00:03:48,872 --> 00:03:49,672
Good.

82
00:03:49,777 --> 00:03:50,350
Excellent.

83
00:03:50,992 --> 00:03:51,513
Bravo.

84
00:03:54,592 --> 00:03:56,432
I heard what you said.

85
00:03:57,155 --> 00:03:58,490
You want us to meet up more often.

86
00:03:58,592 --> 00:03:58,992
Exactly.

87
00:03:59,190 --> 00:04:00,000
I'll make it happen.

88
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:01,193
Good.

89
00:04:01,313 --> 00:04:01,872
Listen.

90
00:04:02,753 --> 00:04:03,473
Next month

91
00:04:04,832 --> 00:04:05,473
is my

92
00:04:06,033 --> 00:04:06,953
70th birthday.

93
00:04:09,193 --> 00:04:11,033
My children insisted on
throwing a party,

94
00:04:11,193 --> 00:04:12,513
so I agreed.

95
00:04:12,577 --> 00:04:13,150
That's great.

96
00:04:13,672 --> 00:04:14,473
When the time comes,

97
00:04:14,552 --> 00:04:16,352
every single one of you here

98
00:04:16,792 --> 00:04:17,832
has to be there.

99
00:04:19,113 --> 00:04:20,673
Good. You must be there.

100
00:04:20,953 --> 00:04:21,472
Of course.

101
00:04:22,311 --> 00:04:23,550
Welcome to my birthday banquet.

102
00:04:24,352 --> 00:04:25,753
A 70th birthday banquet.

103
00:04:25,955 --> 00:04:27,222
Who hasn't been to one before?

104
00:04:29,673 --> 00:04:33,513
But as for a 70th birthday banquet
combined with a wedding,

105
00:04:33,753 --> 00:04:34,993
we've never been to before.

106
00:04:37,152 --> 00:04:38,313
Right, a wedding.

107
00:04:38,673 --> 00:04:39,832
Yeah.

108
00:04:40,352 --> 00:04:40,832
Right?

109
00:04:41,155 --> 00:04:42,750
A wedding should be held
on the same day.

110
00:04:42,753 --> 00:04:45,633
Everyone, get your red packets ready.

111
00:04:46,553 --> 00:04:47,753
Get it ready.

112
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:49,433
Okay.

113
00:04:51,433 --> 00:04:53,272
Did you propose to her just now?

114
00:04:54,513 --> 00:04:54,792
No.

115
00:04:54,792 --> 00:04:55,753
I was helping her

116
00:04:56,073 --> 00:04:57,592
with her wound.

117
00:04:59,873 --> 00:05:00,352
Listen.

118
00:05:00,352 --> 00:05:01,712
Today's a great opportunity.

119
00:05:02,272 --> 00:05:03,553
Make this class reunion

120
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:04,553
more exciting.

121
00:05:04,673 --> 00:05:05,673
Propose to her

122
00:05:06,352 --> 00:05:07,272
in front of everyone.

123
00:05:10,832 --> 00:05:11,673
I'm not ready yet.

124
00:05:11,673 --> 00:05:12,912
That's settled.

125
00:05:13,592 --> 00:05:14,272
Wait, you...

126
00:05:14,272 --> 00:05:14,873
Hurry.

127
00:05:21,630 --> 00:05:22,822
Everyone, take your seats.

128
00:05:24,352 --> 00:05:25,832
Shen has something to say.

129
00:05:26,753 --> 00:05:27,313
Come on.

130
00:05:29,232 --> 00:05:30,272
Let me take a drink first.

131
00:05:35,466 --> 00:05:36,177
Don't worry.

132
00:05:37,513 --> 00:05:38,993
An important announcement?

133
00:05:44,032 --> 00:05:44,912
Yes, pretty important.

134
00:05:49,832 --> 00:05:50,873
He's giving a speech.

135
00:05:50,873 --> 00:05:51,712
Let's all quiet down.

136
00:05:52,152 --> 00:05:52,633
Yilian.

137
00:06:01,232 --> 00:06:01,792
Yilian.

138
00:06:06,553 --> 00:06:07,073
I...

139
00:06:16,472 --> 00:06:18,152
I packed some osmanthus cake.

140
00:06:18,790 --> 00:06:20,644
Make sure to bring it back to Lian Jin.

141
00:06:24,152 --> 00:06:24,993
All right.

142
00:06:24,993 --> 00:06:26,032
He's thoughtful.

143
00:06:26,630 --> 00:06:27,444
Such a gentleman.

144
00:06:27,792 --> 00:06:28,073
Come.

145
00:06:28,513 --> 00:06:29,673
Let's drink.

146
00:06:29,832 --> 00:06:30,472
Come on.

147
00:06:32,032 --> 00:06:32,313
Cheers.

148
00:06:38,433 --> 00:06:39,392
Don't hit me.

149
00:06:39,392 --> 00:06:40,513
Come on.

150
00:06:50,666 --> 00:06:52,088
I think Lian Jin's still up.

151
00:06:53,313 --> 00:06:55,553
I'll get you some hot water
for a foot bath.

152
00:06:55,953 --> 00:06:56,673
All right.

153
00:06:57,313 --> 00:06:57,633
Go on.

154
00:06:57,912 --> 00:06:58,472
Lian Jin.

155
00:06:59,313 --> 00:06:59,592
Mom.

156
00:07:01,555 --> 00:07:02,070
Look at this.

157
00:07:02,070 --> 00:07:02,622
What's it?

158
00:07:03,032 --> 00:07:05,152
Mr. Shen packed this for you.

159
00:07:05,832 --> 00:07:06,633
It's still warm.

160
00:07:07,590 --> 00:07:08,311
Osmanthus cake.

161
00:07:08,313 --> 00:07:09,232
Your favorite.

162
00:07:09,792 --> 00:07:10,792
Two whole boxes. Look.

163
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:16,044
Eat it while it's fresh.

164
00:07:19,232 --> 00:07:20,272
Is he trying to bribe me

165
00:07:21,433 --> 00:07:23,193
so that he can take my dear mom away?

166
00:07:26,592 --> 00:07:28,073
What are you talking about?

167
00:07:31,953 --> 00:07:33,589
Mr. Shen really cares about you.

168
00:07:33,590 --> 00:07:35,422
You can't always assume the worst.

169
00:07:37,310 --> 00:07:38,377
He must be after something.

170
00:07:38,592 --> 00:07:39,433
Everyone does.

171
00:07:40,753 --> 00:07:41,392
Don't you?

172
00:07:41,553 --> 00:07:41,832
I...

173
00:07:41,910 --> 00:07:43,111
I'm not after something?

174
00:07:43,352 --> 00:07:44,472
I just want you to be healthy

175
00:07:44,673 --> 00:07:45,712
and happy, is that okay?

176
00:07:51,310 --> 00:07:54,066
- Is this the furniture repair service?
- My son...

177
00:07:54,710 --> 00:07:55,555
I want to fix a bed.

178
00:07:56,472 --> 00:07:58,269
Yes. We bought one from you.

179
00:07:58,270 --> 00:07:59,777
My kid isn't sleeping well on it.

180
00:08:00,466 --> 00:08:01,266
You can come over?

181
00:08:01,352 --> 00:08:02,229
Thank you so much.

182
00:08:02,230 --> 00:08:02,977
Look at that.

183
00:08:03,673 --> 00:08:04,433
Look at Mr. Shen.

184
00:08:05,590 --> 00:08:06,577
He's thoughtful.

185
00:08:07,032 --> 00:08:08,792
We had already finished

186
00:08:10,912 --> 00:08:11,953
eating everything.

187
00:08:12,352 --> 00:08:14,592
But Mr. Shen still ordered this for you.

188
00:08:15,953 --> 00:08:18,032
He ordered two boxes.
He said you like this.

189
00:08:19,430 --> 00:08:20,555
You're not grateful about it?

190
00:08:21,073 --> 00:08:21,753
That's not right.

191
00:08:22,266 --> 00:08:23,510
If you don't want to eat it now,

192
00:08:23,513 --> 00:08:24,272
have it later.

193
00:08:28,673 --> 00:08:29,912
Stop overthinking.

194
00:08:39,992 --> 00:08:41,112
We all love you.

195
00:08:41,872 --> 00:08:42,592
Understand?

196
00:08:49,510 --> 00:08:50,177
All right.

197
00:08:52,911 --> 00:08:55,288
Get out of the bed and move a little
after reading books.

198
00:08:55,333 --> 00:08:56,770
I'll leave the osmanthus cakes here.

199
00:08:56,822 --> 00:08:58,155
Don't wait until it gets cold.

200
00:08:58,512 --> 00:08:59,273
All right, Mom.

201
00:09:03,190 --> 00:09:03,933
Don't touch it.

202
00:09:03,953 --> 00:09:04,512
I'll do it.

203
00:09:20,752 --> 00:09:22,033
Rub it like this.

204
00:09:22,955 --> 00:09:23,688
Is this okay?

205
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,273
Did Lian Jin

206
00:09:28,110 --> 00:09:29,155
like the osmanthus cakes?

207
00:09:29,752 --> 00:09:31,112
Yes, he loves it.

208
00:09:31,673 --> 00:09:32,793
He told me to thank you.

209
00:09:34,433 --> 00:09:35,673
I like this boy.

210
00:09:37,073 --> 00:09:38,273
He's quiet.

211
00:09:40,712 --> 00:09:41,832
Tell him

212
00:09:42,313 --> 00:09:44,232
to think of this place as home.

213
00:09:44,793 --> 00:09:46,512
Don't always coop himself up
in his room.

214
00:09:46,793 --> 00:09:47,752
He should come out more.

215
00:09:49,112 --> 00:09:50,153
That's how he is.

216
00:09:50,752 --> 00:09:52,393
He's reticent.

217
00:09:53,752 --> 00:09:55,112
Honestly, I'm to blame.

218
00:09:56,913 --> 00:09:58,273
I was too busy back then

219
00:09:58,311 --> 00:09:59,466
that I had neglected him.

220
00:09:59,650 --> 00:10:01,310
I worked day and night shifts
back to back,

221
00:10:01,313 --> 00:10:02,433
leaving him alone at home.

222
00:10:03,033 --> 00:10:04,673
Even when he wasn't feeling well,

223
00:10:05,310 --> 00:10:07,111
he wouldn't say anything.
He just endured it.

224
00:10:07,155 --> 00:10:08,244
He didn't want to bother me.

225
00:10:08,752 --> 00:10:09,832
That's how his nephritis

226
00:10:09,832 --> 00:10:11,352
missed the best time for treatment.

227
00:10:14,752 --> 00:10:15,472
I've stayed single

228
00:10:16,313 --> 00:10:17,632
all these years

229
00:10:18,433 --> 00:10:20,153
because I was afraid he'd be mistreated.

230
00:10:21,953 --> 00:10:23,953
But later, I looked for support

231
00:10:23,953 --> 00:10:25,153
because I thought

232
00:10:25,644 --> 00:10:27,533
I couldn't take care of him
on my own.

233
00:10:27,673 --> 00:10:28,472
I'm really scared.

234
00:10:29,632 --> 00:10:31,712
Scared that if his condition worsens,

235
00:10:31,733 --> 00:10:34,377
it'll turn into kidney failure,
and things will become more difficult.

236
00:10:37,153 --> 00:10:37,673
Sit.

237
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:39,533
Don't always squat.

238
00:10:43,953 --> 00:10:44,592
Listen to me.

239
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:47,592
From now on,

240
00:10:48,352 --> 00:10:50,712
we'll take care of him together
as his parents.

241
00:10:52,112 --> 00:10:53,232
The boy is still young.

242
00:10:54,830 --> 00:10:57,622
We should find the right doctor
and the right hospital for him.

243
00:10:58,992 --> 00:11:00,832
Don't worry about the money.

244
00:11:01,193 --> 00:11:03,073
I've taken on plenty of lectures.

245
00:11:04,190 --> 00:11:05,155
They'll pay me.

246
00:11:05,433 --> 00:11:06,433
He's young.

247
00:11:07,033 --> 00:11:08,433
He'll recover well.

248
00:11:09,430 --> 00:11:10,088
Definitely.

249
00:11:19,377 --> 00:11:20,830
My white hairs are showing again.

250
00:11:26,832 --> 00:11:27,832
Yilian, listen to me.

251
00:11:30,310 --> 00:11:31,266
We've been together

252
00:11:32,913 --> 00:11:34,712
for quite some time, right?

253
00:11:38,033 --> 00:11:39,992
Can we take the next step

254
00:11:41,953 --> 00:11:43,193
and register our marriage?

255
00:11:47,232 --> 00:11:48,073
I'd love to.

256
00:11:48,512 --> 00:11:49,193
That's good.

257
00:11:49,712 --> 00:11:50,153
But...

258
00:11:51,472 --> 00:11:51,913
But

259
00:11:53,712 --> 00:11:55,869
as you see, Lian Jin

260
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:57,430
takes time to get familiar with people.

261
00:12:01,112 --> 00:12:02,193
I want him to have more time

262
00:12:03,313 --> 00:12:04,352
to adjust first.

263
00:12:08,872 --> 00:12:09,433
So,

264
00:12:10,632 --> 00:12:11,273
can we

265
00:12:12,150 --> 00:12:13,333
wait a little longer?

266
00:12:13,953 --> 00:12:14,273
Yes.

267
00:12:15,393 --> 00:12:15,992
Of course.

268
00:12:16,273 --> 00:12:17,352
I understand.

269
00:12:18,712 --> 00:12:18,992
Well.

270
00:12:19,273 --> 00:12:20,352
We'll wait.

271
00:12:21,230 --> 00:12:21,933
It's okay.

272
00:12:22,230 --> 00:12:22,844
You're so kind.

273
00:12:27,992 --> 00:12:28,953
You're so kind to me.

274
00:12:29,673 --> 00:12:30,273
Phone call.

275
00:12:31,033 --> 00:12:31,393
Pick up.

276
00:12:32,992 --> 00:12:34,193
What are these?

277
00:12:34,433 --> 00:12:35,553
Who's that in those photos?

278
00:12:35,913 --> 00:12:36,313
Look.

279
00:12:36,632 --> 00:12:37,913
When were these taken?

280
00:12:38,433 --> 00:12:39,953
During our gathering. Look.

281
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:41,110
So many pictures.

282
00:12:41,273 --> 00:12:42,472
Look at me. I laughed.

283
00:12:47,200 --> 00:12:48,200
(Dad's Moments
A romantic day)

284
00:12:57,832 --> 00:12:59,512
Let me show you something interesting.

285
00:12:59,872 --> 00:13:01,273
- I saw it.
- Look.

286
00:13:01,913 --> 00:13:03,953
Dad knows how
to use a photo retouching app.

287
00:13:04,712 --> 00:13:05,632
Duole taught him.

288
00:13:06,070 --> 00:13:07,155
To keep up with the times.

289
00:13:07,553 --> 00:13:08,112
That's good.

290
00:13:08,273 --> 00:13:08,953
What about you?

291
00:13:09,155 --> 00:13:10,750
Why don't you keep up with the times?

292
00:13:12,313 --> 00:13:13,872
I fall behind, okay?

293
00:13:14,073 --> 00:13:15,232
Oh, please.

294
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:18,433
Your dad learned filters for Ms. Lian.

